comment: Green (GSW) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Harden's (HOU) shot attempt.
Livingston (GSW) and Motiejunas (HOU) make incidental contact with one another during rebounding.
Beverley (HOU) intentionally kicks the ball on the play.
Thompson (GSW) sets the screen on Motiejunas (HOU) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Beverley (HOU) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Clark (GSW) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Motiejunas (HOU) sets the screen on Iguodala (GSW) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Thompson (GSW) makes incidental contact with Ariza (HOU) that does not affect his RSBQ.
Green (GSW) maintains legal guarding position and does not affect Ariza's (HOU) shot attempt.
Green (GSW) sets the screen on Harden (HOU) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
[Observable in enhanced video] RHH shows that Harden (HOU) makes contact with Livingston's (GSW) arm that affects his driving shot attempt.
Harden (HOU) pushes Green (GSW) in the back affecting his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Green (GSW) dislodges Beasley (HOU), affecting his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Green (GSW) sets the screen on Ariza (HOU) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Motiejunas (HOU) legally contests Thompson's (GSW) jump shot attempt.
[Incidental or immaterial] Green (GSW) is in the paint for longer than three seconds.
Clark (GSW) makes incidental contact with Beverley (HOU) that does not affect his RSBQ.
Clark (GSW) cleanly knocks the ball away from Beasley (HOU).
Iguodala (GSW) clamps and holds Beasley's (HOU) arm on the inbound pass.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that possession be awarded to HOU was upheld.
Harden (HOU) initiates the contact with Iguodala (GSW) to create space and dislodges him from his legal guarding position.
Howard (HOU) maintains legal guarding position on Speights (GSW) during the inbound pass.
Green (GSW) wraps Beasley (HOU) and throws him to the ground on the inbounds play. Basketball Operations is reviewing the contact.
